ism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705192,"age":48,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705193,"age":57,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Roger FitzRoger was born in 1280, in Cheshire, England, his father, Aaron John FitzRoger, was 19 and his mother, Margaret Speeton, was 21. He had at least 1 son with Emma. He died in 1365, in Chester, Cheshire, England, at the age of 85."},"et":{"1280–1365":"1280–1365","1280–Female":"1280–Surnud","1300–Male":"1300–Surnud","1300–1365":"1300–1365","1261–1301":"1261–1301","1259–1313":"1259–1313","1261":"1261","1280":"1280","1290":"1290","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1259":"1259","1313":"1313","1301":"1301","1300":"1300","1365":"1365","1453":"1453","ABT 1300":"umbes 1300","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England","Chester, Cheshire, England":"Chester, Cheshire, England","England":"England","Stapleford, Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England"},"fi":{"1280–1365":"1280–1365","1280–Female":"1280–Kuollut","1300–Male":"1300–Kuollut","1300–1365":"1300–1365","1261–1301":"1261–1301","1259–1313":"1259–1313","1261":"1261","1280":"1280","1290":"1290","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1259":"1259","1313":"1313","1301":"1301","1300":"1300","1365":"1365","1453":"1453","ABT 1300":"noin 1300","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England","Chester, Cheshire, England":"Chester, Cheshire, England","England":"England","Stapleford, Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England"},"fr":{